Phase X: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
Full blockage, robbing out and dumping.

Locus 65 is the soil below the blockage within the eastern north niche (part of Locus 82) of the bathroom. The soil is a fine loose silt/sand (Munsell 10 YR 4/3 brown), with inclusions of plaster, pottery, glass, small stones and bone. The soil is likely the result of dumping for the filling in of the niche just before its blockage. Locus 65 is therefore phased to Stage 5.
